org.eeml.math.expr

Class ComplexNumber

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eeml.math.expr.ComplexNumber

  • public class ComplexNumber
extends java.lang.Object
    This class mainly implements the math expression complex number including methods like add, multiply etc.The naming principle is the same as java.math.BigInteger. Maintained byEEML.see more oneeml.github.io
    Since:
    v1.0.0
    Author:
    EULIR

      • transferable

        public boolean transferable()
        To judge whether the complex number can be transferred into a double value. When this complex number has no imaginary part, we can say it is transferable.
        Returns:
        true if the complex number is transferable, false otherwise.

      • toDouble

        public double toDouble()
        Transfer the complex number into the double value. If and only if the complex number is transferable can it be successfully be changed(the complex number should have no imaginary part when it can be transferred). Therefore, the method transferable should almost always be called before calling method toDouble.
        Returns:
        double value of real part of this complex number.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - when this complex number has imaginary part.
